President Obama has declared a major disaster in North Dakota due to flooding that began on February 14, 2011. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. The declaration covers multiple counties, tribes, and reservations in the state. Willie G. Nunn has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA.